---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="What Juli's Cookbook is and how to use it.">
  <div class="text-page">
    <h1>About this cookbook</h1>

    <p>
      Juli's Cookbook is a personal recipe collection - a place where I collect the dishes I actually cook
      and share them with the people I care about.
    </p>

    <h2>How to use it</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Browse all recipes on the <a href={`${base}recipes`}>Recipes</a> page.</li>
      <li>Use the filter buttons to narrow by diet, meal type, cuisine, or time.</li>
      <li>Click any recipe card to open the full recipe - ingredients, method, and all.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What's here</h2>
    <p>
      Recipes I've cooked enough times that I trust them. Each one has a short description that explains
      what the dish is actually like - not the marketing version, but the real one. Sourced from cookbooks,
      websites, and videos, always credited.
    </p>

    <h2>How it's built</h2>
    <p>
      Static site built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a>,
      hosted on GitHub Pages. New recipes go live within a minute or two of me pushing a commit.
      No server, no database - just files.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
